look_out = Song.create(title: "Look Out", trt: "04:23", notes: "<p>First released in 2010, this track has been remixed and remastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music in 2016.</p>", lyrics: "<p>It&rsquo;s been clear for years, but we kept up appearances.</p>\r\n<p>Caught you pining to hear the lines interferences.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;re a million miles away. Who you looking out for?</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s nothing, it&rsquo;s no one you say. Who you looking out for?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I cracked open the lock, that sealed your nothings away.</p>\r\n<p>I thought I&rsquo;d stake stock of what these relics portray.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I show you the note, you sway. Who you looking out for?</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s nothing, it&rsquo;s no one you say. Who you looking out for?</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;re a million miles away. Who you looking out for?</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;re fading so much each day. Who you looking out for?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You were missing from sleep. I should be used to your disappearances.</p>\r\n<p>What is it you seek in the crawl space&rsquo;s clearances?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tell me now.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>What voices cause you to stray? Who you looking out for?</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s nothing, it&rsquo;s no one you say. Who you looking out for?</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;re a million miles away. Who you looking out for?</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;re fading so much each day. Who you looking out for?</p>", song_order: 5, album_id: ef_volume_one.id)
reach = Song.create(title: "Reach", trt: "03:50", notes: "<p>This song is about the future archaeologist that helped start The Earthly Frames. First released in 2010, this track has been remixed and remastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music in 2016.</p>", lyrics: "<p>The sails subside.</p>\r\n<p>The witness deny the wreaths he lays in.</p>\r\n<p>The counting.</p>\r\n<p>The carrying.</p>\r\n<p>The blessings of tin.</p>\r\n<p>The circling crow.</p>\r\n<p>The idle foe, the lanes they stay in.</p>\r\n<p>The self-contained.</p>\r\n<p>The brief distain for the places we&rsquo;ve been.</p>\r\n<p>The heckling dove.</p>\r\n<p>The Easter shove.</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ve reached back again.</p>\r\n<p>The cresting wave.</p>\r\n<p>The lost arcade.</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ve reached back again.</p>\r\n<p>The lesson lost.</p>\r\n<p>The evening frost.</p>\r\n<p>The phantom&rsquo;s last limb.</p>\r\n<p>The sharpened call.</p>\r\n<p>The falling wall.</p>\r\n<p>The reigns have been trimmed.</p>\r\n<p>Now I know that you know the cause of my grin.</p>\r\n<p>Now I know that you know you&rsquo;ve reached back again.</p>\r\n<p>The painted peach.</p>\r\n<p>The second bleach.</p>\r\n<p>The bruised last limb.</p>\r\n<p>The shadow kite.</p>\r\n<p>The harbor's site growing ever so dim.</p>\r\n<p>Now I know that you know the cause of my grin.</p>\r\n<p>Now I know that you know you&rsquo;ve reached back again.</p>", song_order: 4, album_id: ef_volume_one.id)
pagans = Song.create(title: "Pagans", trt: "02:35", notes: "<p>Original by James Toth/The Blood Group. I played hurdy gurdy on the original track and was fascinated by James' mastery of lyrics here. Such a brilliant song writer. This recording was released in 2012, then remixed and remastered in 2016 by Alan Douches at West West Side Music.</p>", lyrics: "<p>On an auto-pilot astral plane full of smugglers who release the strain of time.</p>\r\n<p>An ownership of sight and sound, drowning beside the box you weighted down.</p>\r\n<p>All the relics from another place traded to merchants to give up your space for time.</p>\r\n<p>Reversal of an outbound sort and constellations that the scopes ignore in.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You'll be knifed and stabbed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A haggard watcher in a gentle place, where pricks and pagans fall and grab new shapes in light.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Those anchors drag the river clean, a privy palace where the boats convene, reveal.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You'll be chased a while. Right now.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You'll be knifed and stabbed. You'll be chased a while, alright.</p>", song_order: 1, album_id: purgatory.id)
pike = Song.create(title: "Pike", trt: "04:15", notes: "<p>James Pike, the subject of this song, has inspired many a Sci-Fi writer including Philip K. Dick and E.L. Doctorow. First released in 2010, this track has been remixed and remastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music in 2016.</p>", lyrics: "<p>The sunlight plays the wrecking ball to the timeline.</p>\r\n<p>Was it last rites or only shades confirmed?</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I know now what I seek to see,</p>\r\n<p>tripping, trapped along the long wadi</p>\r\n<p>Right now I see you crawl from the Dead Sea.</p>\r\n<p>So you tell me if this be heresy</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>My son, my son, my holy ghost.</p>\r\n<p>The moonlight sands, our only host.</p>", song_order: 2, album_id: ef_volume_one.id)
good_as_gold = Song.create(title: "Good As Gold", trt: "05:39", notes: "<p>My family often makes fun of how cryptic I tend to be. This song was me wearing it on my sleeves. First released in 2010, this track has been remixed and remastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music in 2016.</p>", lyrics: "<p>And are we still awake?</p>\r\n<p>There are things I have to say.</p>\r\n<p>Been thinking what&rsquo;s at stake.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Hear me and decide, then we&rsquo;ll say that at least we tried.</p>\r\n<p>I don&rsquo;t know how we hide, look out the window, you can&rsquo;t deny</p>\r\n<p>As this house settles into stone, it&rsquo;s like a soldier whose coming home.</p>\r\n<p>I don&rsquo;t know if it will stand &rsquo;til were old, that&rsquo;s when you say &lsquo;We&rsquo;re good as gold.&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For years every step outside seemed a trap, every telephone ring - a chance to snap.</p>\r\n<p>But I hope you know, you&rsquo;re my way back.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>And of course you&rsquo;re so very right, for you to question my second sight.</p>\r\n<p>What good is just to see only misstep and misery?</p>", song_order: 3, album_id: ef_volume_one.id)
conflict = Song.create(title: "An Unfortunate Conflict of Evidence", trt: "02:41", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>My brain&rsquo;s laced and ready to go</p>\r\n<p>The lost Mind is already in stow</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve been broadcasting in Mclear</p>\r\n<p>hoping that Contact is near</p>\r\n<p>It was Arbitrary&rsquo;s survey</p>\r\n<p>when I was born and then betrayed</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve been broadcasting in Mclear</p>\r\n<p>hoping that Contact is near</p>", song_order: 3, album_id: conjurer.id)
program = Song.create(title: "Program", trt: "03:51", notes: "<p>I had borrowed this album from Tim Dedman and was completely obsessed with it for a summer long ago. Original by Supercollider.&nbsp;Mastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music.</p>", lyrics: "<p>my arms are wrapped in cotton</p>\r\n<p>and you know i can&rsquo;t pick up anything</p>\r\n<p>news program station manager</p>\r\n<p>abundant light one thousand burning white dots</p>\r\n<p>he pulls her hair like heaven&rsquo;s strings unwinding</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>see the course unwinding</p>\r\n<p>obstruction</p>\r\n<p>i can&rsquo;t stand my surprise</p>\r\n<p>my untied shoelace</p>\r\n<p>run: mysticism [mysterious]</p>\r\n<p>run: nine colors</p>", song_order: 3, album_id: purgatory.id)
end_timed =Song.create(title: "End Timed Family", trt: "02:50", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>Elsewhere, a foam soldier shakes a leg&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>at a hundred-million critical masses&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Begging little wanderers, please, to come home&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I have a twin sister operating from a railway&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>at the apex of a foreign structure.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You shall see nothing more satisfactory than&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>when they are inclined to do so.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Farthest blue of the sky is weighted down by the sun. Each day&rsquo;s close brings some token of yours, pushed to the shore and attacking the sand.</p>", song_order: 7, album_id: light.id)
everybody = Song.create(title: "Everybody Wants to Rule the World", trt: "03:54", notes: "<p>I tried to recreate how this well known song sounded to me when I first heard it as a kid.&nbsp;Mastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music</p>", lyrics: "<p>Welcome to your life</p>\r\n<p>There's no turning back</p>\r\n<p>Even while we sleep</p>\r\n<p>We will find You acting on your best behavior</p>\r\n<p>Turn your back on mother nature</p>\r\n<p>Everybody wants to rule the world</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It's my own desire</p>\r\n<p>It's my own remorse</p>\r\n<p>Help me to decide</p>\r\n<p>Help me make the most Of freedom and of pleasure</p>\r\n<p>Nothing ever lasts forever</p>\r\n<p>Everybody wants to rule the world</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There's a room where the light won't find you</p>\r\n<p>Holding hands while the walls come tumbling down</p>\r\n<p>When they do, I'll be right behind you</p>\r\n<p>So glad we've almost made it</p>\r\n<p>So sad they had to fade it</p>\r\n<p>Everybody wants to rule the world</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I can't stand this indecision</p>\r\n<p>Married with a lack of vision</p>\r\n<p>Everybody wants to rule the world</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Say that you'll never, never, never, need it</p>\r\n<p>One headline, why believe it?</p>\r\n<p>Everybody wants to rule the world</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>All for freedom and for pleasure</p>\r\n<p>Nothing ever lasts forever</p>\r\n<p>Everybody wants to rule the world</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Written by Chris Hughes, Ian Stanley, Roland Orzabal &bull; Copyright &copy; EMI Music Publishing, Warner/Chappell Music, Inc, BMG Rights Management US, LLC</p>", song_order: 4, album_id: purgatory.id)
thread = Song.create(title: "The Conjurer's Thread", trt: "04:25", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>Hoisted high now,</p>\r\n<p>they&rsquo;re waiting for you to come down</p>\r\n<p>What&rsquo;s good is gone</p>\r\n<p>and gone is what they long to be</p>\r\n<p>No compliments</p>\r\n<p>for the broken instruments</p>\r\n<p>A scream is heard</p>\r\n<p>and herded toward the back is she</p>\r\n<p>In the top stall</p>\r\n<p>a butcher starts a brawl</p>\r\n<p>And thrown is he</p>\r\n<p>toppling from the balcony</p>\r\n<p>At the house&rsquo;s mercy</p>\r\n<p>the conjurer&rsquo;s thread grows bare</p>\r\n<p>Call for the understudy</p>\r\n<p>have you seen him anywhere?</p>\r\n<p>At the house&rsquo;s mercy</p>\r\n<p>not one step ahead</p>\r\n<p>Call for the confederates</p>\r\n<p>at least they know they&rsquo;re misled</p>\r\n<p>Let them stare through</p>\r\n<p>no impromptu</p>\r\n<p>What did they pay for?</p>\r\n<p>What did they stay for?</p>\r\n<p>Let them burn through</p>\r\n<p>there&rsquo;s no trick to undo</p>\r\n<p>What did they pay for?</p>\r\n<p>What did they stay for?</p>", song_order: 1, album_id: conjurer.id)
sigils = Song.create(title: "Everyday Sigils", trt: "04:16", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>I&rsquo;m casting signs for you.</p>\r\n<p>Believe me, I tried all the tricks in the booking</p>\r\n<p>and nothing else is due.</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m acting out for you</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve picked up the tic of the extra in passing</p>\r\n<p>and now the past is staged too.</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m watching out for you.</p>\r\n<p>Out of the corner of my eye the mirror was glancing, are those reflections coming through?</p>\r\n<p>Everyday my symbols tremble</p>\r\n<p>My burnt intentions I&rsquo;ve tossed to the air</p>\r\n<p>But in every way my meanings crumble</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m stuck at the border, nothing to declare.</p>\r\n<p>I lay in wait for you.</p>\r\n<p>Hunched down in the seat, I fell into trancing and now I missed the queue</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m losing track of you</p>\r\n<p>I can&rsquo;t hear the words I thought you were asking. In ringing ears a circle grew</p>\r\n<p>Everyday my symbols tremble</p>\r\n<p>The words they twist like the braids in your hair</p>\r\n<p>But in every way my meanings crumble</p>\r\n<p>Was there ever a chance that you would care?</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve read all about ships in passing</p>\r\n<p>But all along I&rsquo;ve been signaling to the air.</p>", song_order: 2, album_id: conjurer.id)
obduration17 = Song.create(title: "Obduration (2017)", trt: "04:11", notes: "<p>Forgive the made up word.&nbsp;Originally written and recorded for Hoarding Eleven in 2011. Remixed in 2017. Mastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music.</p>", lyrics: "<p>It&rsquo;s a well worn truth, now what they say that anger turned inward will whittle you away.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Obduration. Odd Duration.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m carving up trenches with my bare hands to capture the river that memory demands.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Obduration. Odd Duration.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A storm is now settling over the lake we float on. I&rsquo;ll stop pretending you took me to bond. You look to shoreline, before you commit there&rsquo;s a bright signal halting your fit.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>", song_order: 3,album_id: hoarding_seventeen.id)
dead_edit = Song.create(title: "Dead Edit", trt: "05:09", notes: "<p>This is really the first time we hear about Haints. Fittingly they come off more as ghosts then latter materialized in <em>Hoarding Eleven</em>. First released in 2010, this track has been remixed and remastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music in 2016.</p>", lyrics: "<p>When the playback won&rsquo;t synch in, you think you&rsquo;ve gone between the frames to the bottom of the bin.</p>\r\n<p>And the shots from the short ends, you&rsquo;ve screened them ten times before, but why not try again?</p>\r\n<p>This is how you begin to see: Time when folded over groans, it begs to let it be.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>They&rsquo;re right behind you.</p>\r\n<p>You strain to hear their notes. You cut to set them free.</p>\r\n<p>How they&rsquo;ve assigned you</p>\r\n<p>Hurry up and execute! Split the reels, reconstitute.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Now how long have they been there? You reverse the reels within your mind and note the empty chair.</p>\r\n<p>As the leader roles off the core, they are pleased with your work, they ask you back for more.</p>", song_order: 1, album_id: ef_volume_one.id)
basty = Song.create(title: "All Basty", trt: "02:58", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>Once again, villagers are shuttering</p>\r\n<p>Crops have failed, children are vanishing</p>\r\n<p>Led astray, seeking more suffering</p>\r\n<p>Apples grow too, in my garden,</p>\r\n<p>you need only to come and see.</p>\r\n<p>No, I won&rsquo;t beg your pardon,</p>\r\n<p>you&rsquo;re the one who exiled me.</p>\r\n<p>Do expect sons to be fantasizing</p>\r\n<p>Scholars weep, there&rsquo;s no end to the dramatizing</p>\r\n<p>Wives, they curse me for you&rsquo;re desiring</p>\r\n<p>As time begins to harden,</p>\r\n<p>you forgot who touched the tree</p>\r\n<p>From the things I&rsquo;ve seen written,</p>\r\n<p>you&rsquo;d think it must be me</p>\r\n<p>All of you, basty, Al Basty!</p>", song_order: 4, album_id: conjurer.id)
bad_luck = Song.create(title: "Strings of Bad Luck", trt: "04:51", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>So, you&rsquo;ve lost all your heroes?</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s time to take it on the chin.</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s no relief from the headline.</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s no thickening your skin.</p>\r\n<p>Our strings of luck have been tangled.</p>\r\n<p>When pearls are off, the swine come in.</p>\r\n<p>They&rsquo;ll make you wish you had bothered</p>\r\n<p>to stash your papers in the tin.</p>\r\n<p>The one that you kept by the fence post,</p>\r\n<p>forever playing guardian.</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s a bitter pill to swallow,</p>\r\n<p>bitter still when swallowed again.</p>\r\n<p>Our strings of luck have been tangled.</p>\r\n<p>When pearls are off the swine come in.</p>\r\n<p>It does not help but to mention,</p>\r\n<p>at best it&rsquo;s just a spoiled win.</p>\r\n<p>They&rsquo;ll make you wish you had bothered</p>\r\n<p>to remember how before had been.</p>\r\n<p>Restring our luck again, restring. We string our luck again, restring.</p>", song_order: 5, album_id: conjurer.id)
mnemonic = Song.create(title: "The Architectural Mnemonics of M. Nodisks", trt: "02:11", notes: "", lyrics: "", song_order: 6, album_id: light.id)
dismantling = Song.create(title: "Dismantling Ubiquitous Monitoring Systems", trt: "02:41", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>Your drone took out half the block and our drummer! Revenge, excess? Oh, what rock have you been living under?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Release, Repeat, Reverse, Delete&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This place is filled with spray-on spies,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>that pretty face ain&rsquo;t hard to recognize&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I think you think that now you&rsquo;ve got our number. But while you filed it all away we&rsquo;ve traced you to your bunker&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This place is filled with spray-on spies,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>that pretty face to hard to disguise</p>", song_order: 5, album_id: light.id)
star = Song.create(title: "Star Filter", trt: "03:21", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>Before</p>\r\n<p>we lose the light and</p>\r\n<p>have to return to</p>\r\n<p>the photograph of where we started</p>\r\n<p>Reassure</p>\r\n<p>me that you&rsquo;ll wear</p>\r\n<p>that metal shirt</p>\r\n<p>you wore when you departed</p>\r\n<p>Filter the stars</p>\r\n<p>their light&rsquo;s too late for us</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s where we are</p>\r\n<p>not the witness</p>\r\n<p>Filter the stars</p>\r\n<p>their light is dead and gone</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s not what we wish</p>\r\n<p>it&rsquo;s what we settle on</p>\r\n<p>Dreams</p>\r\n<p>we had back in school</p>\r\n<p>they&rsquo;re growing dimmer now</p>\r\n<p>betrayed, off and carted</p>\r\n<p>Remind</p>\r\n<p>me of the story you told</p>\r\n<p>about the roaring ships</p>\r\n<p>that made the sky again uncharted</p>", song_order: 6, album_id: conjurer.id)
outer = Song.create(title: "The Outer Loop", trt: "04:23", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>Round and round the city of dead dreams</p>\r\n<p>Encased in glass and steel and bright head beams</p>\r\n<p>All now is stopped. There&rsquo;s a wreck ahead it seems.</p>\r\n<p>I remember throwing my key.</p>\r\n<p>Off to follow Aomame.</p>\r\n<p>Cut the engine and I will flee.</p>", song_order: 10, album_id: conjurer.id)
abandoner = Song.create(title: "Abandoner", trt: "04:39", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>Release the ballast!</p>\r\n<p>Reason&rsquo;s gone, the way, I shall list:</p>\r\n<p>Now there&rsquo;s nothing here,</p>\r\n<p>no way to sort the tether from the sphere</p>\r\n<p>And the deck is stacked</p>\r\n<p>against the day and those it contracts</p>\r\n<p>Out here we&rsquo;ll melt,</p>\r\n<p>no sun to care about where we&rsquo;ve knelt</p>\r\n<p>Do this for me once before I go and lose my confidence</p>\r\n<p>Do this another time</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m the abandoner, guilty of the crime</p>\r\n<p>Do this, I&rsquo;m begging you</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ll wave goodbye, I&rsquo;ll forget them too</p>\r\n<p>Once more I&rsquo;ll ask you this,</p>\r\n<p>What chains the chains hanging from your wrists?</p>\r\n<p>I don&rsquo;t want to stay and make it better</p>\r\n<p>You won&rsquo;t see me here or hereafter</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ll flee from spring and head to winter</p>\r\n<p>Abandon, Abandoner.</p>", song_order: 8, album_id: conjurer.id)
seat =Song.create(title: "A Seat at the Rainbow Table", trt: "03:02", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>We are planning to break in this week</p>\r\n<p>while legal bores the red team to sleep</p>\r\n<p>Gapped off, tails up, we are ready for the shriek!</p>\r\n<p>Will you please tell us what you find</p>\r\n<p>while scraping the depths for a sign?</p>\r\n<p>What monsters to root and disable</p>\r\n<p>while sitting at the rainbow table?</p>\r\n<p>Your handle will be etched in the lore</p>\r\n<p>while I got traced dropping off of Tor</p>\r\n<p>I think I hear the windbreakers at my front door</p>", song_order: 9, album_id: conjurer.id)
rsi = Song.create(title: "RSI Labeling Act", trt: "03:00", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>You&rsquo;re playing this song now, what does that say?</p>\r\n<p>Endorsement of the obscure or 48kHz?</p>\r\n<p>The mix is too noisy, there&rsquo;s too much delay.</p>\r\n<p>Does it mean what it was or what you want it to be? Let&rsquo;s agree that it is so there&rsquo;s something to see. Now what was the difference between what was shown, the things in our heads, and what can be known?</p>\r\n<p>What have I sold you? What commodity?</p>\r\n<p>Microtransactions of culture debris?</p>\r\n<p>Or is it the exchange and the chance to agree?</p>\r\n<p>I don&rsquo;t know myself, so how could you know me?</p>\r\n<p>Does it mean what it is or is it the other way?</p>\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s agree that it is so there&rsquo;s something to say.</p>\r\n<p>Speaking in riddles and some concepts on loan,</p>\r\n<p>then why bother sharing this blood from a stone?</p>", song_order: 7, album_id: conjurer.id)
old = Song.create(title: "The Old Revolution", trt: "03:26", notes: "<p>The last verse, a damn fine one, was omitted as in this cover it felt <em>done</em>.</p>", lyrics: "<p><strong>Words and Music by Leonard Cohen</strong></p>\r\n<p>I finally broke into the prison,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I found my place in the chain.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Even damnation is poisoned with rainbows,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>all the brave young men&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>they're waiting now to see a signal&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>which some killer will be lighting for pay.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Into this furnace I ask you now to venture,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>you whom I cannot betray.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I fought in the old revolution&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>on the side of the ghost and the King.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Of course I was very young&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>and I thought that we were winning;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I can't pretend I still feel very much like singing&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>as they carry the bodies away.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Into this furnace I ask you now to venture...&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Lately you've started to stutter&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>as though you had nothing to say.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To all of my architects let me be traitor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Now let me say I myself gave the order&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>to sleep and to search and to destroy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Into this furnace I ask you now to venture...&nbsp;</p>", song_order: 2, album_id: purgatory.id)
time = Song.create(title: "Time Moving in Light", trt: "04:11", notes: "", lyrics: "", song_order: 12, album_id: light.id)
eye = Song.create(title: "Eye on Ghost Singers", trt: "03:12", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>Bill and I took in the late show to hear my voice come out of you. Outside the theater there&rsquo;s a fault line. We could sink before our song is through.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tomorrow I&rsquo;m singing at a christening.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You know there&rsquo;s no dancers in the pew.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You never came to lunch last Monday. That setting&rsquo;s still sitting there unused. Here&rsquo;s Sid ringing about a dubbing. Needed me for Mitzi, I said he was confused. Everyone knows I only work for you now, &rsquo;till there&rsquo;s no more voice to be removed</p>", song_order: 11, album_id: light.id)
getting_started =Song.create(title: "Getting Started in Tempography", trt: "02:42", notes: "", lyrics: "", song_order: 10, album_id: light.id)
dark = Song.create(title: "A Dark Years History", trt: "02:42", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>At your earliest convenience&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ll accept your banishment&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sitting in the dark, waiting&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>hoping you&rsquo;ll appear&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sitting in the dark, waiting&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>above the atmosphere&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sitting in the dark, waiting&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>for years and years and years&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sitting in the dark, waiting&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>until it&rsquo;s very clear&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sitting in the dark, waiting&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>for two light years&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sitting in the dark, waiting&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>until you volunteer&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sitting in the dark, waiting&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>until I persevere&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sitting in the dark, waiting&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>until I disappear</p>", song_order: 9, album_id: light.id)
wind = Song.create(title: "A Teleological Wind", trt: "03:08", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>There&rsquo;s Mr. Wind&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>He&rsquo;s at it again&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s Mr. Sky&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>making sure you don&rsquo;t fly&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s Mr. Sun&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>what&rsquo;s done can&rsquo;t be undone&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve rearranged&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>the cause and the effect&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Assigning you names&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>my little world will stay in check&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A calcified tale&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>you all must respect&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You can&rsquo;t hide the nail from the architect&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s Mr. Wind&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>He&rsquo;s at it again&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s Mr. Moon&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>leaving so soon&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s Mr. Sun&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>He knows he&rsquo;s won&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>And the winner takes it all&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>till the other stars fall&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve rearranged&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>the sound and the sight,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>the bellow and the wind,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>the torch and the light</p>", song_order: 8, album_id: light.id)
imagined = Song.create(title: "The Imagined Lives of Shirley Kudirka", trt: "03:13", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>She&rsquo;s okay with the way she looks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>She&rsquo;s disappointed by the second hook.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>What she wrote, it&rsquo;s okay, but it&rsquo;s never going to make a careful listener&rsquo;s day.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>She&rsquo;s okay with the way it feels.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>She&rsquo;s not surprised when he makes her kneel.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Left alone a while, now to remember why she even liked his little, turgid smile&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>See her looking with her eyes closed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>See her looking like nobody knows&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>that the movie was better than the book,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s worse than it looks&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>She&rsquo;s okay with the way sounds&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Purple vinyl spinning round and round&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Autographed, &ldquo;To under hood&rdquo; not sure she ever really understood.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>See her looking with her eyes closed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>See her looking like nobody knows&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>that the movie was better than the book,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>its meaning something we all mistook</p>", song_order: 4, album_id: light.id)
harmonics = Song.create(title: "Underrepresented Harmonics", trt: "03:34", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>It&rsquo;s not too loud, it&rsquo;s merely deafening,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>the way the straight and narrow fall and send the past trembling&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The frogs, the lobsters they do venerate&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>they will burn too, no more ash heap for them to renovate&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tall, white columns topple down most every day. I&rsquo;d like nothing more than to just get out of the way.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The barricades are open, sand lies under stone. When you forge the world anew, you&rsquo;re next in line to dethrone.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s poison in the cradles, jet fighters in the lake. So go now and tear up fables, just don&rsquo;t take the bait.</p>", song_order: 2, album_id: light.id)
huay = Song.create(title: "Huayranchina", trt: "1:18", notes: "<p>One of the first examples of recorded pollution came from a glacial ice-core sample from Peru. Some traces of bismuth burned in, presumably Incan, bronze smelting forges were captured in the ice. The piece takes its name from this type of forge, which is named for the god of wind.</p>", lyrics: "", song_order: 3,album_id: empty.id)
warming = Song.create(title: "Just Warming Up", trt: "8:16", notes: "<p>This music comes directly from NOAA&rsquo;s archive of monthly surface temperatures. The data per month, year, and decade are used to generate MIDI notes and then fed through analog and digital synthesizers. The source code <a href=\"https://github.com/brotherclone/just-getting-warmed-up\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">can be found on Github</a> for those looking to create their own temperature-based music.</p>", lyrics: "", song_order: 4,album_id: empty.id)
met =Song.create(title: "Met with Great Malthusianism", trt: "1:34", notes: "<p>This track is a meditation on our misguided responses, past, and future, to the Anthropocene.</p>", lyrics: "", song_order: 5,album_id: empty.id)
reading = Song.create(title: "Reading Frame Shift", trt: "2:53", notes: "<p>Genetic mutation is the means life uses to ensure adaptation to the environment. It ends mostly in cancer. I imagined the mutation process as a general loss of audio fidelity and a randomly repeating sample in this recording. The strings from &ldquo;M.E.E.&rdquo; were copied and fed through a Morphagene eurorack module using off-synch L.F.O.s to create a chaotic governing of the sample size, playback rate, and range.</p>", lyrics: "", song_order: 6,album_id: empty.id)
fish = Song.create(title: "Fish Nor Fowl", trt: "2:12", notes: "<p>Small, repetitive percussion patterns, over forty in total, were overlaid to create a fluttering landscape. As with &ldquo;Just Warming Up,&rdquo; I imagined the percussive hits measuring the ecosystem. Each ping a species dying off forever. Slowed bird calls, fed through a rock-and-roll guitar set up adds some nihilistic flair.</p>", lyrics: "", song_order: 7,album_id: empty.id)
newton = Song.create(title: "Newton", trt: "04:45", notes: "<p>full-on Sussex County, NJ remorse</p>", lyrics: "<p>We walked the streets of Newton. The year was ninety-three. I asked you what class you cut. You asked me to let you be, &ldquo;You know, the moon is covering the only thing to see&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Look to the ceiling as it fades away It was just a feeling, another weekday</p>\r\n<p>From his porch, an old man heard us and spilled his herbal tea. He screamed, and rose, and fell, again, and called to us from his knees &ldquo;If I catch you shits 'round here again, you&rsquo;ll be hanging from that tree&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>And so we carried on in my Shadow, north on Twenty-Three I asked you if you&rsquo;d seen a ghost. You said you&rsquo;d seen enough of me.</p>\r\n<p>Look to the ceiling as it fades away Who knows what you&rsquo;re feeling, it&rsquo;s hard to say</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s no more revealing what led us astray It was just a feeling, another weekday</p>", song_order: 5, album_id: ruine.id)
space = Song.create(title: "It Used To Be Space, Now itâ€™s Here", trt: "03:38", notes: "<p>coming back to New York in 2005 and being lost.</p>", lyrics: "<p>I forgot I was walking south without the towers in sight I could swear it was right by Ear, but I must not be right</p>\r\n<p>This street? This block? Retreat? Jaywalk? Circles and circles. Keep walking.</p>\r\n<p>Was it across from the park? Where John met his Mark?</p>\r\n<p>Or off Dekalb Ave? Where Nicky the Knife got stabbed?</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s not there no more.</p>", song_order: 4, album_id: ruine.id)
tangier = Song.create(title: "Tangier", trt: "04:22", notes: "<p>with sincere hope to the people of Tangier Island.</p>", lyrics: "<p>Soft shell in the ghost trap waiting for a pull that never comes</p>\r\n<p>Golf carts float upside down out near where the markers washed away</p>\r\n<p>Rot tide tugs pilings down That dock is buoyed up by prayers alone</p>\r\n<p>The outside men they talk of carbon, they talk of apes They say the waters will rise and that there is no escape Well, the waters killed the Pharaoh&rsquo;s men Sometimes you have to drown the world to start it back up again</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s his will, it&rsquo;s his order One nation cried underwater</p>\r\n<p>This town ain&rsquo;t built upon stone Settled bones sleep through the airish &lsquo;morn</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ll stay, I&rsquo;ll never leave Until the island is swallowed whole</p>\r\n<p>All gone, swept away like a third of the stars in the heavens</p>", song_order: 3, album_id: ruine.id)
search = Song.create(title: "Search Flares", trt: "03:34", notes: "<p>over the fortress wall, a minefield.</p>", lyrics: "<p>I&rsquo;d be lying to you if I said I knew the way</p>\r\n<p>Why didn&rsquo;t we keep with the group? Why did we have to stray?</p>\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s stop here for tonight They won&rsquo;t get us, the cold just might</p>\r\n<p>Search flares are falling dark the perimeter has been marked</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s no more room for discovery Gone from rescue to recovery</p>\r\n<p>Do you remember why we came here? You never struck me as a sightseer.</p>\r\n<p>Well strike me down if I lie once more Until I lay on the forest floor</p>\r\n<p>Search flares are falling dark the perimeter has been marked</p>\r\n<p>Call it off, cancel the calvary Gone from rescue to recovery</p>", song_order: 9, album_id: ruine.id)
empty_fields = Song.create(title: "The Empty Fields", trt: "4:19", notes: "<p>The album concludes with a quartet piece. Hazy memories of pastoral, Jusid soundtracks fading and degrading into pizzicato death rattles. As if it wasn&rsquo;t obvious already, this recording leaves you with a final, passing comment, &ldquo;Ladies and gentlemen, we are quite fucked.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<dl>\r\n<dt>Maria Grigoryeva</dt>\r\n<dd>violin, viola, additional engineering</dd>\r\n<dt>Lyudmila Kadyrbaeva</dt>\r\n<dd>cello</dd>\r\n<dt>Zoltan Renaldi</dt>\r\n<dd>double bass</dd>\r\n</dl>", lyrics: "", song_order: 8,album_id: empty.id)
here = Song.create(title: "Here Comes the Mechanical Bride", trt: "04:36", notes: "<p>made from commercials I was exposed to at a young age.</p>", lyrics: "<p>Keep your mind as busy as your mouth. Don&rsquo;t be shy, it&rsquo;s what it&rsquo;s all about. She looks great even this close up</p>\r\n<p>Here she comes, walking down the aisle All-wheel drive and a bright white smile She&rsquo;s here to spray away the stains you fight each day</p>\r\n<p>Champions of love, proceed, proceed, Valued customers draw near and feed, We&rsquo;ve only just begun to bend and bleed</p>\r\n<p>Sink your teeth, this thing could be real, Pure love in a box of cereal If you trust your judgment, you could be Dodge material</p>\r\n<p>Here she comes, she&rsquo;s all bows and curls Let us thank the heavens for those little girls Time to obey your thirst betcha you blush first</p>\r\n<p>Champions of love, proceed, proceed, Valued customers draw near and feed, We&rsquo;ve only just begun to proceed to feed</p>\r\n<p>Give in! Give in! Give in to the taste!</p>", song_order: 8, album_id: ruine.id)
sleeve = Song.create(title: "Sleeve", trt: "05:22", notes: "<p>bodies used in astral projection have rights too, you know.</p>", lyrics: "<p>I used to meet you by the stream Hidden there where my tent would lean I never knew the age that you seemed And your signal flags what did you mean?</p>\r\n<p>Didn&rsquo;t you mind being taken until I did awaken?</p>\r\n<p>Didn&rsquo;t you mind being flayed until my role was played?</p>\r\n<p>Nothing to believe Nothing up my sleeve</p>\r\n<p>On your dark side of the river We would set out to deliver A mark against the flow of time Before I heard the third bell chime</p>\r\n<p>Didn&rsquo;t you mind being used until the stone refused?</p>\r\n<p>Nothing to believe Nothing up my sleeve</p>", song_order: 10, album_id: ruine.id)
the_mark17 = Song.create(title: "The Mark (2017)", trt: "03:25", notes: "<p>Originally written and recorded for <em>Hoarding Eleven </em>in 2011. Remixed in 2017. Mastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music.</p>", lyrics: "<p>You take the light, I&rsquo;ll take the dark.</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ll set the tower, you float the ark.</p>\r\n<p>This game&rsquo;s afoot and you&rsquo;re the mark.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Three squares up, or maybe four?</p>\r\n<p>Time to play another round.</p>\r\n<p>Toy ships land on paper shores.</p>\r\n<p>Your token calls for a state of war.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tap the deck. Unlock the score.</p>\r\n<p>Tiny houses topple to the floor.</p>\r\n<p>Have you forgotten what you&rsquo;re going for?</p>\r\n<p>Surrender now, they implore.</p>\r\n<p>Have you forgotten who you&rsquo;re holding for?</p>\r\n<p>Have you forgotten who you&rsquo;re hoarding for?</p>", song_order: 1,album_id: hoarding_seventeen.id)
vacant17 = Song.create(title: "Vacant Lands (2017)", trt: "03:30", notes: "<p>Originally written and recorded for Hoarding Eleven in 2011. Remixed in 2017. Mastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music.</p>", lyrics: "<p>Memory triangulates, trapping me in the din of this roadside scene.</p>\r\n<p>A conjuring sheet, a map of men who wait behind every word I&rsquo;ve ever read.</p>\r\n<p>Who knows who plants the seeds that grow into this long-coming scheme?</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s the inner lock now open for them to see, for them to take, for them to remake in their image of me.</p>\r\n<p>I thought at least that I could trust in myself. I thought I knew where to stand. But now I think with a limp and I walk down the path toward the vacant lands.</p>", song_order: 2,album_id: hoarding_seventeen.id)
evening17 = Song.create(title: "Evening Ladies (2017)", trt: "04:21", notes: "<p>Originally written and recorded for Hoarding Eleven in 2011. Remixed in 2017. Mastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music.</p>", lyrics: "<p>Did you note me driving?</p>\r\n<p>I followed the only path I saw.</p>\r\n<p>Can&rsquo;t you see I&rsquo;m trying?</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m just looking for a little awe.</p>\r\n<p>Feels like years I&rsquo;ve been out here, putting up with signs.</p>\r\n<p>Hoping for a broken scaffold and for the sun to resign</p>\r\n<p>When the night comes to drown the flashes of the day</p>\r\n<p>don&rsquo;t leave me with these road side horrors, they come up to stay.</p>\r\n<p>Did you write down what I did, mark it in your book?</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s nothing easy about knowing the steps you mistook.</p>\r\n<p>For years I&rsquo;ve been out here, putting up with signs</p>\r\n<p>Hoping for a broken scaffold and for the sun to resign</p>", song_order: 4,album_id: hoarding_seventeen.id)
