broken = Song.create(title: "Broken Front Tooth", trt: "04:16", notes: "<p>Vocals by Remez. Ted pulled a gun at Scott's house. Judy judy had to be carried out. Dawn and Gordon break-in for art class. Abbey's smile.</p>", lyrics: "<p>Do I mind if you stop by? Well, damn straight! You&rsquo;re my alibi. And, not for nothing, see if I care. You know this place is dead and the whole damn town, they already stare.</p>\r\n<p>Can&rsquo;t you see that tar and feather is meant for me? Don&rsquo;t you need another friendly face for you to read?</p>\r\n<p>There&rsquo;s a house by your boyfriend&rsquo;s stash The glass is broken and TV smashed. There&rsquo;s a typewriter on the second floor that never wrote &ldquo;Nothing and nothing no more.&rdquo; They wrote &ldquo;Nothing&rdquo; and nothing no more</p>\r\n<p>Just remember when you stop by I&rsquo;ll be on the floor pretending I died And, not for nothing, see if I care You know I&rsquo;m not sticking &lsquo;round, I&rsquo;m leaving town with my half of the share.</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s not true - the brutality of youth. A car mirror cracked and a broken front tooth. These reflections weren&rsquo;t meant to last, the Captain sees land but is tied to the mast</p>", song_order: 2, album_id: ruine.id)
moon = Song.create(title: "Moonrakers", trt: "02:46", notes: "<p>an overture of sorts. memory, space, and identity are going to be mushed for this one.</p>", lyrics: "<p>What it seems may not be where a hidden beam falls on your hair.</p>\r\n<p>Scrape the waves, and shoot the flare. Moonlight bathes what wasn&rsquo;t there It wasn&rsquo;t there.</p>\r\n<p>But we knew then the end was soon. Time don&rsquo;t bend, so rake the moon.</p>\r\n<p>Years ago, I knew none, except the glow, a braid undone.</p>\r\n<p>Kept away, kept for fun. You did stay. While I did run. I did run.</p>\r\n<p>I knew this road.I knew this room. Well, time don&rsquo;t slow, so rake the moon.</p>", song_order: 1, album_id: ruine.id)
cloak = Song.create(title: "Cloakroom", trt: "02:00", notes: "", lyrics: "", song_order: 9, album_id: pulsar.id)
tell = Song.create(title: "Tell", trt: "03:06", notes: "<p>apologies to Mr. Lydon, Marvel Comics, and divorced dudes everywhere.</p>", lyrics: "<p>Didn&rsquo;t you tell me that you&rsquo;d been here before? You recognized the door?</p>\r\n<p>I know you came here looking to finish off this final chore. But I thought it was more.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;We&rsquo;re getting reports of violence interrupting the second shift. Digging to resume.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;re getting closer five more meters to breach the veil.</p>\r\n<p>Does she know her moves in this world break up nations? Does she know her words in this world bring damnation?</p>\r\n<p>I can see from your eyes this won&rsquo;t go very well. It&rsquo;s always been your tell. You are so lovely even as you turn to leave. If only you could believe.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Call back your men the levels are too high.&rdquo; &ldquo;Fall back! Fall back!&rdquo; &ldquo;There&rsquo;s something coming through&rdquo; &ldquo;There&rsquo;s something wrong with the sky.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Did she know her path in this world break up nations? Did she know her thoughts in this world bring damnation?</p>", song_order: 7, album_id: ruine.id)
newest = Song.create(title: "Newest of the Natural Senses", trt: "04:07", notes: "<p>2062 is also a rough year. Vocals by Marvin Muonek&eacute;</p>", lyrics: "<p>Back in sixty-two We were losing ground and the rent was due</p>\r\n<p>Took a flyer down Medical study, seen it &lsquo;round town</p>\r\n<p>Change the way you see it&rsquo;s your opportunity</p>\r\n<p>Change the way you hear it could be the cure</p>\r\n<p>So why not try to help? Plus some pocket coin to help myself</p>\r\n<p>Signed away my rights Filled out the form with my loved one's dislikes</p>\r\n<p>Take it once a day Take it with no food</p>\r\n<p>Call without delay &lsquo;Till the study concludes</p>\r\n<p>Now what you see is what you get, what you get, what you get when you&rsquo;re barely looking You call and cry, you scream until you forget, you forget, you forget what you were really seeing</p>\r\n<p>Can you remember Those songs you knew before?</p>\r\n<p>Photos and letters Now blank on your living room floor</p>\r\n<p>On the sixteenth day My eyes went dark and I started to sway</p>\r\n<p>Then I tried to scream I felt held down by something unseen</p>\r\n<p>Did I hear my name? It sounded familiar, but not quite the same</p>\r\n<p>Blind or future sight Can&rsquo;t see now, but I see tomorrow&rsquo;s light</p>", song_order: 6, album_id: ruine.id)
waits = Song.create(title: "She Waits For Yesterday", trt: "03:33", notes: "", lyrics: "<p>Goodbye, good luck my darling, don&rsquo;t forget your secret mission. Don&rsquo;t panic when the process is starting, prepare yourself for superposition.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Now, settle down your sensor membrane.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I think you know this venture&rsquo;s insane and the pleasure stream won&rsquo;t broadcast for long.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>See, time won&rsquo;t let you center-maintain&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dispensing lives like St. Germain&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The future is present, now it&rsquo;s your rite to wrong.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Again this time&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Again aligned to fall&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is the way the arrow stalls&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Again this time&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Again aligned to fall&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is the way the sleeper recalls&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I know it&rsquo;s late, Kate, but you can&rsquo;t hesitate&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You can&rsquo;t go where they stray, you have to wait for yesterday.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Decoherence!&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Again this time&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Again aligned to fall&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is the way the hero grows small</p>", song_order: 3, album_id: light.id)
doorbell = Song.create(title: "A Doorbell for Finite Beings", trt: "03:34", notes: "<p>Read the debut video coverage on <a href=\"https://substreammagazine.com/2018/11/premiere-earthly-frames-doorbell-finite-beings/\">Sub-Stream Magazine</a>.</p>", lyrics: "<p>Block the left side</p>\r\n<p>from the right side</p>\r\n<p>by lifting the door</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Usher the cold</p>\r\n<p>Usher the heat</p>\r\n<p>don&rsquo;t even the score</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve been watching, I&rsquo;ve been tracking</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve tried to tell you that something was lacking</p>\r\n<p>Let it come through, let it come through</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Was that your doorman, I passed down the block?</p>\r\n<p>Can you text him I&rsquo;m coming? Leave the keys in the box</p>\r\n<p>Or maybe tomorrow, I&rsquo;ve lost track of the time</p>\r\n<p>It won&rsquo;t take long sorting your stuff from mine</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Block the right side</p>\r\n<p>from the left side</p>\r\n<p>don&rsquo;t let them through</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Usher the heat</p>\r\n<p>Usher the cold</p>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;re gonna split them in two</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Found an old photo, while I was cleaning up</p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s still flowing, from when you spilled the cup</p>\r\n<p>Miscalculations from being so close up</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve been watching, I&rsquo;ve been tracking</p>\r\n<p>I&rsquo;ve tried to tell you that something was lacking</p>\r\n<p>Let them come through, let me come through</p>", song_order: 1, album_id: light.id)
feel =Song.create(title: "Feel Better Soon", trt: "04:47", notes: "<p>Recorded during quarantine with care.</p>", lyrics: "<p>What was it your dad used to say, when you were a kid and dudes dropped every day? Something about enzymes and keys And that the cure is just waiting for the disease</p>\r\n<p>We checked in on him last week with the window cracked, you could just hear him speak.</p>\r\n<p>I asked him which bug was worse. Did he miss the rush and that other nurse? &lsquo;He&rsquo;s a vent jockey now, he's probably cursed.&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>Please tell him feel better soon I hope you feel better soon Please we need you all to stick around We need the good ones to stick around</p>\r\n<p>I know it&rsquo;s strange with me here and you away I&rsquo;m a sad excuse, getting sadder every day. But I&rsquo;ll do my best to hold things down We&rsquo;re all counting the days till you&rsquo;re back in town</p>\r\n<p>Please tell her feel better soon I hope you feel better soon</p>", song_order: 1, album_id: 2)
mee = Song.create(title: "M.E.E.", trt: "11:40", notes: "<p>Written during the quarantine months of the pandemic, &ldquo;M.E.E.&rdquo; (Mass Extinction Events) renders life&rsquo;s rise and fall at the epoch level. My son was working on his seventh-grade science homework and while trying to help him memorize Ordvocian, Devonian, Triassic, Jurassic, Paleogene - a strange melody kept repeating in my head. First, I thought it was &ldquo;Ring Around the Rosie&rdquo; - not quite. Trying to get this melody down in my clumsy, drawn MIDI was my first attempt at composing for a quartet. I added my own harmonium and processing to the piece and then sent the sheet music to some &ldquo;real&rdquo; musicians for the recording. Essentially, &ldquo;M.E.E.&rdquo; is two epochs, with the traces of the first part being side-chained through the second. Each era terminates with exploring the science-homework melody.</p>\r\n<dl>\r\n<dt>Maria Grigoryeva</dt>\r\n<dd>violin, viola, additional engineering</dd>\r\n<dt>Lyudmila Kadyrbaeva</dt>\r\n<dd>cello</dd>\r\n<dt>Zoltan Renaldi</dt>\r\n<dd>double bass</dd>\r\n<dt>Gabriel Walsh</dt>\r\n<dd>harmonium, tapes</dd>\r\n</dl>", lyrics: "", song_order: 1,album_id: empty.id)
rocks = Song.create(title: "Where There are Rocksâ€¦", trt: "6:16", notes: "<p>While working M.E.E. I had a dream in which two tectonic plates were grinding against one another. The rock turned molten along the fault line, and from it arose a sort of consciousness, violent and cunning. I began &ldquo;constructing&rdquo; the piece with two deep bass lines. The parts were identical, except that one was flipped backward. This often created wobbling, dissonant intervals. I then used a contact microphone on stones to build the underworldly ambiance. The piece&rsquo;s name comes from Alan Watts:</p>\r\n<blockquote>&ldquo;Where there are rocks, watch out! Watch out because the rocks are going to eventually come alive, and they are going to have people crawling over them. It is only a matter of time, just in the same way the acorn is eventually going to turn into the oak because it has the potentiality of that within it.&rdquo;</blockquote>", lyrics: "", song_order: 2,album_id: empty.id)


